    "attributes": {
        "action": "Urge Sri Lanka to allow the burial of Covid victims to respect religious beliefs",
        "additional_details": "Covid-19 is a worldwide pandemic with global authorities such as the World Health Organisation advising on matters of burial for those who have been diagnosed with Covid-19 and later died.\r\n \r\nThe recent acts of the Sri Lankan government discriminate against those whose religious beliefs are against being cremated.\r\n \r\nThis against official advice which determines a normal burial alone will suffice with no need for cremation.",
        "background": "The UK government should urge the Sri Lankan Government to allow Covid victims to be buried according to their religious beliefs and not cremated.",
